20:17.495 --> 20:21.920
know what the house was like? It was a very big tree, 
a very beautiful tree. It was very big, like this,

20:26.706 --> 20:30.591
that tree that grew there in the corner of Salabor. 
So my father, I don't know, he bought sheets, what

20:32.033 --> 20:38.601
do you call it? Sheet. Do you know what a sheet is? 
Well, so he bought it. So my father built a house.

20:47.093 --> 20:52.041
The kitchen was big, he made the house like that. 
So, I remember, we all went, we all took, we all went

20:54.004 --> 21:02.737
to that place, but there was no house. But as it 
were, there was this tree. And

21:04.239 --> 21:12.392
then, well, my father was very good, but Entonces, 
mi papá, yo agarré una cobija. ¿Ves? Yo no estaba

21:19.004 --> 21:21.032
muy grande, pero... I grabbed a blanket and I tied 
it on the floor. My father didn't like that I tied

21:26.161 --> 21:28.464
that blanket on the floor. He grabbed one of those 
sticks that hit the mules. I tried to run so they

21:36.575 --> 21:43.624
wouldn't hit me because I was sitting on the 
blanket, but he didn't like that. He said to my

21:43.664 --> 21:49.872
father, I'm going to run, and my father did this and 
I fell. Well, then when I fell down, he told me, you

21:50.054 --> 21:56.100
shouldn't have run, he said. Well, I was going to 
tell you not to throw that mattress on the ground.

22:04.810 --> 22:08.794
It was all I remember that my father was going to hit 
me. Because my father never cursed us, nor did he

22:10.696 --> 22:17.563
ever do us wrong for him. He built that house, and 
then we would step on it. We would step on the

22:22.888 --> 22:27.513
cotton, corn, whatever it was. And he would plant a 
lot of garden all

22:28.254 --> 22:34.923
the time. So he would make us work. There was a lot of 
harvest, a lot of cotton, because the water would

22:37.746 --> 22:45.616
come and the cotton would grow a lot. So he would 
say, They would grab the plow and we would work

22:46.923 --> 22:49.409
here. They would grab the plow, all of us. There was 
a lot of grass. He would help us and guide us and give

22:57.086 --> 23:04.543
us encouragement and everything. Well, I grew up 
with cotton. My father used to sell cotton bags. I

