because they need help to lift up the debris that

32:16.907 --> 32:28.422
there was from the chubasco. And all the neighbors 
from there left. They came from many places to help

32:31.847 --> 32:33.810
there. But you looked at it as if it had been a town. 
You looked at how many things there were there. So

32:44.066 --> 32:53.139
the police were taking care of it because there 
were many things of value thrown away. And then

32:53.160 --> 32:56.805
they checked them all, those who were going to help 
them checked them. They didn't bring anything.

32:59.487 --> 33:07.897
But I'm not saying that I'm in favor of my parents or 
anything. But my parents taught us to respect

33:07.997 --> 33:11.160
others. And they respected me because I never told 
them to bring anything to the house. From what was

33:16.145 --> 33:18.268
there, no. I never saw anything. I never knew 
anything because they never brought anything.

33:25.945 --> 33:34.678
Well, then, after a short time, all of that, for a 
long time, they kept raising all of that. After a

33:34.698 --> 33:39.746
short time, we left from there. We all left for that 
ranch that still exists, but the owners don't.

33:46.175 --> 33:49.220
Here it is, it was Jose Yaliva. After that, from 
that ranch, We went to... what is the 9th street?

34:02.252 --> 34:03.775
It's the 9th street and we were there. Do you know 
where the 9th street is? 37, number 37. Hey

34:09.025 --> 34:14.374
Virginia, is the 9th street, what number is it? 
It's the 9th street. That's how we named it. That's

34:21.443 --> 34:24.066
how we named it. That's how we named it. That's how 
we named it. That's how we named it. That's how we

34:38.503 --> 34:44.130
named it. Yes, but she was Italian. Yes, she was 
Italian. Her wife was Mexican. She was a very

34:53.091 --> 34:56.074
beautiful lady. And they were very nice. So they 
had a house because they were the first founders of

34:59.738 --> 35:07.046
Corpus. So my father and they went to that place 
because that man told him, Gonzales, I don't know

35:14.722 --> 35:23.069
how they would fix it, but he said he would pass his 
land to him so he could plant it. Like my father, he

35:25.131 --> 35:43.868
already had everything, so he said, well, but I 
don't have a house, he said, but I have a little

35:25.131 --> 35:43.868
house, and that little house only had a room, as 
long as here, and the kitchen was divided, and it

35:25.131 --> 35:43.868
was small. He said, there you go, he said, in the 
meantime, he said, but it's very good land, and

35:44.118 --> 35:51.388
it's enough. So he said, my dad, it's good. And so we 
went to that place. So it was on the other side of

36:00.741 --> 36:07.910
that place, there was another land, and it was from 
another Italian. Yes. Yes, they were... The only

36:10.493 --> 36:16.684
friends of the other Italians were friends. So 
they had a very nice house because those families

36:17.205 --> 36:23.617
were the first ones. They had a two-story house 
that still exists. It was a two-story house, so my

36:29.798 --> 36:37.449
father was very close to them. They were very close 
since my father came here and met all of that

36:37.469 --> 36:41.995
family.

36:44.599 --> 36:49.045
They had their parents from those Italians. They 
were very young, both of them. My father and mother

36:53.291 --> 36:56.196
were this size. Both of them were old. But they 
didn't know any Spanish, but they were always

36:58.469 --> 37:04.845
good. And my father had a very good friendship with 
them. When my father needed something, He would go

37:15.378 --> 37:19.624
with him. When my father needed to borrow money, 
the man, that cigarette, would lend money to my

37:19.684 --> 37:29.958
father until the year was over. When the year was 
over, with what my father raised, he would pay 200,

37:29.978 --> 37:42.415
300 pesos to that man, with what my father raised, 
to live with us. Bueno, entonces cuando él tenía

37:43.897 --> 37:49.401
trabajo, mi papá, He was going to work with him. 
When he didn't have money, he was going to work with

37:51.379 --> 37:54.162
him. He helped him a lot. My father really liked to 
play in the barrage. They really liked to play in

37:59.910 --> 38:04.156
the barrage, the Italians. They looked for my 
father. My father, the day he didn't work, he was up

38:05.878 --> 38:15.271
until one in the morning, at four, with them, 
playing in the barrage. They had a very good time

38:15.351 --> 38:18.054
with them. He was... They were two brothers, they 
were Italians. They loved my father very much.

38:25.512 --> 38:30.744
Well, then, they helped us all the time. If he said, 
Hey, Fernando, are you going? Because my father's

38:39.004 --> 38:42.388
name was Fernando. So he said, I want you to lend me a 
boy so that I can roll the cotton or whatever. So my

38:48.955 --> 38:56.985
father says, well, you know, the boys are busy 
here, but if you want, my girl is going to help you.

38:57.005 --> 38:58.667
Oh, that's good, Fernando. We make the roll and all 
that. Well, I was going to roll the work that they

39:01.859 --> 39:07.085
wanted, I was going to do it. Well, then he had two 
girls, that man had, his name was Juan, the other

39:09.007 --> 39:21.700
one was called Rocky and the other one was called 
Juan. So my father treated the older one, who was

39:21.720 --> 39:26.446
Juan. Well, then he says he had, Three

39:30.918 --> 39:34.563
girls. And those girls, they were average, those 
girls. Only one of them was the oldest. So, they

39:43.294 --> 39:50.884
grew up, well, not much, but they were always big, 
the oldest. Because they didn't let me, like now,

39:52.163 --> 39:58.210
they didn't let me play a lot. They only gave me a 
certain amount of time to play with my friends.

40:05.279 --> 40:07.882
That was one friend. My cousin was another friend 
because my aunt lived next door to those Italians.

40:21.762 --> 40:32.481
Y mi prima, pues casi era de la camada mía, pues 
tendría yo creo como algunos once o doce años,

40:21.762 --> 40:32.481
nosotros las tres. At that time, the girl was 
Italian. She had long hair and a beautiful family

40:38.744 --> 40:44.853
braid. I went to my mother and asked her, Lupita, 
will your mother let you come to my house? I said, I

40:50.902 --> 40:54.688
don't think so, because I'm working. She said, I'm 
going to tell your mom. And she came early. And she

40:58.050 --> 41:04.604
said, Mrs. Juanita, let Lupita go play with me for a 
little while. And Trinda, my cousin, said, well,

41:04.624 --> 41:09.735
she said, mom, well, go. She said, but just for a 
little while, Lupe. Half an hour. or Asina. We used

41:15.958 --> 41:17.941
to go and play together. I used to play with the 
other cousin for a little while, either at her

41:17.981 --> 41:22.748
house or at my house. For a little while, and then 
we'd go home. Lupita would say, well, I'm leaving.

41:28.156 --> 41:29.538
I'd go home soon. But it wasn't all the time. It was 
only once a week. Or on Sundays, I'd do everything I

41:35.166 --> 41:43.018
could, and I'd have it on Sundays, but it was at my 
house, and my friends would go there. to play with

41:43.370 --> 41:49.215
me, because I really liked the ball game. And I 
still like the ball

41:49.235 --> 41:56.662
game. And then, well, she begged a lot, that year 
that we were there, she begged a lot, my little

41:56.762 --> 42:12.195
friend, my mom and my dad, because my dad was in 
charge. Entonces dice, ¿por qué no la dejan ir a

42:13.053 --> 42:17.876
Lupita que vaya a la escuela? Yo nunca he ido a la 
escuela. Nunca. Why not? Because the schools were

42:22.320 --> 42:28.372
retired. They weren't very retired, but the 
parents were always stricter. In short, the

42:33.481 --> 42:40.034
parents in those years didn't know what one could 
be missing. Not even one could think of that.

42:45.892 --> 43:05.177
Entonces, de allí estaba retirado, no estaba muy 
retirado, pero podíamos ir a pie como íbamos

42:45.892 --> 43:05.177
entonces, porque cuando esa amiguita me animó y a 
mi papá que me dejara ir, que me dejara ir a la

42:45.892 --> 43:05.177
escuela, entonces me dijo, pues está bueno que 
vaya a la escuela, dijo mi papá y mi mamá, pues que

42:45.892 --> 43:05.177
vaya a la escuela. Pues que entonces ella estaba 
bien contenta porque allí no había amiguitas para

43:06.098 --> 43:15.730
que fueran de allí de ese barrio para que fueran con 
ella, nomás yo, mi prima y mi primo. So, we went to

43:16.452 --> 43:19.695
the school. That school was made by Mr. Jose Jante. 
They told him. He was my father's boss. He made that

43:33.529 --> 43:37.373
school, which is on the way down. I don't know if it 
will be closed. On the way down, there is a school on

43:39.295 --> 43:44.620
the same road. So we went to school and she had a lot 
of white friends, but she didn't leave us. She

44:00.446 --> 44:04.752
always ran and talked with us. Before leaving, she 
would go to the street and tell me, Lupita, because

44:05.187 --> 44:22.892
there was a mountain there, a little bit of a 
mountain, and she had my flip-flops, and I would

44:05.187 --> 44:22.892
get together with my cousin, and there weren't 
many Mexicans, so she would say, Lupita, No te

44:22.872 --> 44:25.835
vayas a ir y me dejes sola. Dice, Lupe, yo te doy un 
sándwich. Dice, pa' que me esperes, me decía. Le

44:31.622 --> 44:34.125
decía yo, pues dile a mi prima. Le decía, si ella me 
espera a mí, entonces yo te espero a ti. No necesito

44:39.512 --> 44:40.913
sándwich. Entonces decía, ay, Lupita, por favor, 
dice, espérame. So I said, well, and I said to my

44:45.839 --> 44:55.289
cousin, let's go, let's go, because she doesn't 
come with us when we're here, she doesn't come with

44:45.839 --> 44:55.289
us, she says, it's better to go. Oh no, I said to her, 
let's wait, poor thing, let's wait. Well, well,

44:59.092 --> 45:02.196
I'm not going to go, I'm going to wait for her. Well, 
then we were waiting for her. And she did go with us.

45:07.541 --> 45:14.428
So when we were going, she was sharing sandwiches 
with us and my cousin always Well, she didn't like

45:14.864 --> 45:17.570
it. So she said, she said, oh, yes, she said, oh, 
don't lick me so much that I don't have a ranch. She

45:25.587 --> 45:30.658
said, she said, my cousin, oh, cousin, why are you 
so bad? I said, well, playing like that, well,

45:30.678 --> 45:34.847
then. Ay, pues que mi primer maestra que ya murió, 
fue primera y última maestra que yo tuve, fue Miss

45:35.536 --> 45:44.610
Bessie. Bueno, esa maestra fue una maestra que 
vino de otros estados, esa maestra.

